# Monefyi PWA - Cursor Rules
# Last Updated: 2025-01-15

## Project Context
project_name: Monefyi
project_type: Progressive Web App (PWA)
primary_language: JavaScript (ES6+)
framework: Vanilla JS (no React/Vue/Angular)
backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Edge Functions)

## Code Style

### JavaScript
- Use ES6+ features (const/let, arrow functions, destructuring)
- Prefer `const` over `let`, never `var`
- Use template literals for strings with variables
- Async/await preferred over `.then()` chains
- Pure functions when possible (no side effects)

### Naming Conventions
- Functions: camelCase with verb prefix (parseQuickText, getUserData, calculateTotal)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_RETRIES, API_ENDPOINT, GRAMMAR_RULES)
- Files: kebab-case.js (parse-rules.js, user-service.js)
- Classes/Types: PascalCase (ParseResult, TransactionModel)

### File Structure
- One primary export per file
- Group related functions together
- Keep files under 300 lines (split if larger)
- Use index.js for barrel exports

### Comments
- JSDoc for all public functions
- Inline comments for non-obvious logic
- TODO comments must include (PHASE-X) prefix
- No commented-out code (use git)

## Error Handling

### Required Pattern
```javascript
async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const result = await apiCall();
    return { success: true, data: result };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Fetch failed:', error);
    Sentry.captureException(error);
    return { success: false, error: error.message };
  }
}
```

### Error Logging
- Use `console.error()` for errors (never `console.log`)
- Send to Sentry for production errors
- Include context (user ID, input, timestamp)
- Never expose sensitive data in logs

## Performance

### Rules
- IndexedDB operations must complete in <50ms
- DOM updates: batch with `requestAnimationFrame`
- Avoid synchronous localStorage (use IndexedDB)
- Debounce user input (300ms for text, 500ms for search)
- Lazy load images `loading="lazy"`

## Security

### Required Checks
- All Supabase queries must use RLS policies
- User input must be sanitized (XSS prevention)
- No sensitive data in localStorage (use IndexedDB + encryption)
- API keys in environment variables (never hardcoded)
- Rate limiting for expensive operations

## Testing

### Requirements
- All public functions need unit tests
- Integration tests for database operations
- E2E tests for user-facing features
- Test coverage target: 70%

### Test Naming
Pattern: "Function/Component - Scenario - Expected Result"
Example: Deno.test('normalizeInput - Amount with "jt" - Converts to millions', ...)

## Database (Supabase)

### Query Patterns
- Select only needed columns (not SELECT *)
- Always handle error from .insert()/.update()
- Use prepared statements (parameterized queries)
- Verify RLS policies for cross-user isolation

## AI Integration

### Prompt Engineering
- Use structured output (JSON schema)
- Include 3-5 few-shot examples
- Set temperature low (0.1-0.3 for deterministic)
- Always check quota before calling
- Fallback to BYOK if quota exceeded

## Feature Flags

### Usage Pattern
```javascript
const useNewFeature = await featureFlags.isEnabled('feature_name', userId);
if (useNewFeature) {
  return await newImplementation();
} else {
  return await legacyImplementation();
}
```

### Rollout Strategy
- Start at 5% (internal team)
- Monitor metrics for 48h
- Increase to 15%, 30%, 50%, 75%, 100%
- Auto-rollback if error rate >2%

## Monefyi-Specific Rules

### Parser Pipeline
- Always try L0-L2 before calling server
- Log all parse events (non-blocking)
- Never block user flow on logging failure
- Cache memory in IndexedDB for offline

### Transaction Fields
- Required: date, type, amount, currency
- Optional: category, merchant, account, notes
- Always validate amount >0
- Date format: ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-DD)

### Confidence Scoring
- L1 Memory: >=0.95
- L2 Rules: >=0.75
- L3 Fuzzy: >=0.65
- L4 AI: >=0.60
- L5 Review: <0.60

## Git Commit Messages

### Format
```
type(scope): Short description

Longer description if needed.

Refs: #issue-number
```

### Types
- feat: New feature
- fix: Bug fix
- refactor: Code change (no behavior change)
- perf: Performance improvement
- test: Add/update tests
- docs: Documentation
- chore: Maintenance (deps, configs)

## When in Doubt

### Reference Docs
Before implementing, check:
- @.monefyi/PARSE_MIGRATION_CONTEXT.md - Overall architecture
- @.monefyi/DECISION_LOG.md - Why decisions were made
- @docs/phases/PHASE_1_FOUNDATION.md - Current phase details
- @docs/reference/GRAMMAR_RULES.ts - Parser patterns
- @docs/testing/GOLDEN_DATASET.json - Test cases

### Attach Context
Always attach when:
- Implementing new feature: @PHASE_X.md
- Using shared types: @TYPES.ts
- Database work: @DB_SCHEMA.sql
- Parser work: @GRAMMAR_RULES.ts
```